{"query": {"pages": {"44356310": {"lastrevid": 639496245, "pageid": 44356310, "canonicalurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arnold_Marshall_Rose", "title": "Arnold Marshall Rose", "editurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Arnold_Marshall_Rose&action=edit", "length": 4834, "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "touched": "2015-03-29T00:49:22Z", "ns": 0, "fullurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arnold_Marshall_Rose", "revisions": [{"*": "<div class=\"hatnote\">For the violinist, see <a href=\"/wiki/Arnold_Ros%C3%A9\" title=\"Arnold Ros\u00e9\">Arnold Ros\u00e9</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background:transparent;text-align:center;\"><span class=\"fn\">Arnold Marshall Rose</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;background:transparent; padding-top:0.225em;line-height:1.1em; padding-right:0.5em;\">Born</th><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;line-height:1.3em;\">\nJuly 2, 1918 <br/><a href=\"/wiki/Chicago,_Illinois\" title=\"Chicago, Illinois\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Chicago, Illinois</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;background:transparent; padding-top:0.225em;line-height:1.1em; padding-right:0.5em;\">Died</th><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;line-height:1.3em;\">\nJanuary 2, 1968<span style=\"display:none\">(<span class=\"dday deathdate\">1968-01-02</span>)</span> (aged&#160;49) <br/><a href=\"/wiki/Minneapolis,_Minnesota\" title=\"Minneapolis, Minnesota\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Minneapolis, Minnesota</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;background:transparent; padding-top:0.225em;line-height:1.1em; padding-right:0.5em;\">Fields</th><td class=\"category\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;line-height:1.3em;\">\nSociology</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;background:transparent; padding-top:0.225em;line-height:1.1em; padding-right:0.5em;\">Institutions</th><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;line-height:1.3em;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Minnesota\" title=\"University of Minnesota\">University of Minnesota</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;background:transparent; padding-top:0.225em;line-height:1.1em; padding-right:0.5em;\">Notable awards</th><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;line-height:1.3em;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/American_Association_for_the_Advancement_of_Science\" title=\"American Association for the Advancement of Science\">AAAS</a> Prize for Behavioral Science Research</td></tr></table>\n<p><b>Arnold Marshall Rose</b> (July 2, 1918 - January 2, 1968) was an American sociologist and politician. He was elected to the <a href=\"/wiki/Minnesota_Legislature\" title=\"Minnesota Legislature\">Minnesota Legislature</a> and to the presidency of the <a href=\"/wiki/American_Sociological_Association\" title=\"American Sociological Association\">American Sociological Association</a> (ASA). He held faculty appointments at <a href=\"/wiki/Bennington_College\" title=\"Bennington College\">Bennington College</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Washington_University\" title=\"Washington University\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Washington University</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Minnesota\" title=\"University of Minnesota\">University of Minnesota</a>. He had a special interest in the study of race relations.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">Biography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Arnold_Marshall_Rose&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Biography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Born in Chicago in 1918, Rose earned several degrees from the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Chicago\" title=\"University of Chicago\">University of Chicago</a>, including undergraduate degrees in sociology and economics, then master's and doctoral degrees in sociology.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ASA_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ASA-1\"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> He served in <a href=\"/wiki/World_War_II\" title=\"World War II\">World War II</a> in the <a href=\"/wiki/Mediterranean_Theater_of_Operations\" title=\"Mediterranean Theater of Operations\">Mediterranean Theater</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MLRL_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MLRL-2\"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup>\n</p><p>As a young man, he assisted <a href=\"/wiki/Gunnar_Myrdal\" title=\"Gunnar Myrdal\">Gunnar Myrdal</a> on <i>An American Dilemma: The Negro Problem and Modern Democracy</i>. He worked at the University of Minnesota from 1949 until his death. He also wrote <i>The Negro in America</i> and <i>The Power Struggle</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Papers_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Papers-3\"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> Studying the issue of race relations, Rose found that racism presented four problems. It limited a society's access to talent and leadership, aggravated social issues like poverty, cost a society money and time to defend, and damaged goodwill between nations.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Brief_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Brief-4\"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> He spent stints as a <a href=\"/wiki/Fulbright_Program\" title=\"Fulbright Program\">Fulbright Professor</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Paris\" title=\"University of Paris\">University of Paris</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Rome\" title=\"University of Rome\" class=\"mw-disambig\">University of Rome</a><sup class=\"plainlinks noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"vertical-align:text-top;white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dispenser.homenet.org/~dispenser/cgi-bin/dab_solver.py?page=Arnold_Marshall_Rose&amp;editintro=Template:Disambiguation_needed/editintro&amp;client=Template:Dn\"><span title=\"Link needs disambiguation. (December 2014)\">disambiguation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> in the 1950s.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MLRL_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MLRL-2\"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup>\n</p><p>Rose was elected to a seat in the <a href=\"/wiki/Minnesota_Legislature\" title=\"Minnesota Legislature\">Minnesota Legislature</a> in 1962. He did not seek another term because he had been diagnosed with cancer by 1966.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Papers_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Papers-3\"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> Rose married sociologist and professor Caroline Baer in 1943.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Papers_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Papers-3\"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> He died in January 1968, shortly after being elected president of the ASA but before beginning his term of office. The organization chose to recognize him as one of its presidents.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ASA_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ASA-1\"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Arnold_Marshall_Rose&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-ASA-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-ASA_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ASA_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www2.asanet.org/governance/rose.html\">\"Arnold Marshall Rose\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/American_Sociological_Association\" title=\"American Sociological Association\">American Sociological Association</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <s